I’d like to see a parameter that turns a block of modules into a Drag and Drop interface when used as a template.

Something like this -

```&lt;!--
  templateType: "email"
  isAvailableForNewContent: true
--&gt;
{% extends "/Email/Extend/main.html" %}


{% block modules interface="d_and_d" %}

  {% module "module_16611548554953" path="/Email/Modules Global/Masthead", label="Masthead" no_wrapper="True" %}
  {% module "module_166131502510790" path="/Email/Modules/Banner", label="Banner" %}
  {% module "module_1661326370554104" path="/Email/Modules/Paragraph and CTA", label="Paragraph and CTA" %}
  {% module "module_1661343853136147" path="/Email/Modules/Signature", label="Signature" %}
	{% module "module_166131505560892" path="/Email/Modules/CTA Highlight", label="CTA Highlight" %}
  {% module "module_166131507429993" path="/Email/Modules/Logo Section", label="Logo Section" %}

{% endblock %}```
Not being able to drag and drop modules is a pain when it comes to using HubSpot.
